1
00:00:44,625 --> 00:00:49,583
♪ opening song ♪

2
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,125
Dismissed.

3
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:50,375
Wanna stop by the café
on the way home?

4
00:02:50,458 --> 00:02:51,083
Yeah, sure.

5
00:02:51,166 --> 00:02:52,166
What about you, Natsuki?

6
00:02:52,250 --> 00:02:53,416
Sorry, I can't.

7
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:54,541
I have to get to work.

8
00:02:54,625 --> 00:02:55,708
Bye!

9
00:02:55,791 --> 00:02:57,125
Whoa, what do you
mean, you have a job?

10
00:02:57,208 --> 00:02:58,375
Girl's full of surprises.

11
00:02:58,458 --> 00:02:59,375
You're kidding me.

12
00:02:59,458 --> 00:03:00,916
Didn't you already
eat your lunch?

13
00:03:09,625 --> 00:03:10,166
Hey!

14
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:11,000
Takumi!

15
00:03:11,083 --> 00:03:12,208
Over here!

16
00:03:12,291 --> 00:03:13,375
--Hey, man.
--Oh, hey, Itsuki.

17
00:03:13,458 --> 00:03:14,916
So what's up?

18
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:15,875
With what?

19
00:03:15,958 --> 00:03:17,125
What do you mean 'with what'?

20
00:03:17,208 --> 00:03:18,916
I'm talking about
your ride, dude!

21
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,750
Oh... I don't know.
It's fine, I guess.

22
00:03:20,833 --> 00:03:24,125
It runs differently, but I can
still drive at my own pace.

23
00:03:24,208 --> 00:03:25,250
I thought... you said it was

24
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:26,625
a real pain
to drive that thing

25
00:03:26,708 --> 00:03:28,958
after the whole engine
being swapped out incident.

26
00:03:29,041 --> 00:03:30,875
Yeah, once the
tachometer was installed

27
00:03:30,958 --> 00:03:32,916
it all changed
pretty drastically.

28
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:35,958
Still, that car is
one fast machine.

29
00:03:38,083 --> 00:03:39,500
Brother, I would
kill to say the same

30
00:03:39,583 --> 00:03:41,958
thing about my car
at least once in my life.

31
00:03:42,041 --> 00:03:44,375
Until then, what about giving
me a ride on the mountain pass.

32
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:45,208
Sure.

33
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:46,333
If you try not to freak out.

34
00:03:46,416 --> 00:03:47,666
What's that supposed to mean?

35
00:03:47,750 --> 00:03:49,291
That you'll probably faint.

36
00:03:49,375 --> 00:03:51,000
Dude, I would not!

37
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:52,250
I'm tougher than you!

38
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:53,833
See! See!

39
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,791
Oh, Takumi.

40
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:14,083
Thank you for your business!

41
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:24,083
Takumi, what are
you two checking out?

42
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:25,458
I, uh...

43
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:28,041
Yeah, I was wondering if
I could ask you a question.

44
00:04:28,125 --> 00:04:29,333
Sure, whatcha got?

45
00:04:29,416 --> 00:04:30,708
I've been watching
you for a while and I wanted

46
00:04:30,791 --> 00:04:32,166
to know how you
learned so much

47
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:34,208
about the ins and
outs of mechanics.

48
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:40,500
How, and I guess you mean
other than working in here.

49
00:04:40,583 --> 00:04:43,208
Well, I guess I tinkered on
motorcycles a lot in high school

50
00:04:43,291 --> 00:04:44,833
with a couple of my buddies.

51
00:04:44,916 --> 00:04:46,375
But once I got my own car,

52
00:04:46,458 --> 00:04:47,708
it became a whole lot more fun,

53
00:04:47,791 --> 00:04:50,041
just knowing that the
entire machine was mine.

54
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:51,625
Honestly, I think
I became familiar

55
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:54,291
with the whole idea of
mechanics before I even knew it.

56
00:04:54,375 --> 00:04:55,625
You seem pretty
interested in the

57
00:04:55,708 --> 00:04:58,000
mechanics side of things too,
aren't you Takumi?

58
00:04:58,083 --> 00:04:59,208
No.

59
00:05:00,250 --> 00:05:02,625
But I've realized something.

60
00:05:02,708 --> 00:05:05,041
Or at least I'm starting to.

61
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:06,375
It's like this...

62
00:05:06,458 --> 00:05:08,291
...after the tachometer
was installed and the

63
00:05:08,375 --> 00:05:10,625
engine was revved up
higher, it was like it

64
00:05:10,708 --> 00:05:13,333
changed the
characteristics of the car.

65
00:05:13,416 --> 00:05:15,416
I didn't expect that a
mechanical change would

66
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:17,500
affect the driving
style that much.

67
00:05:17,583 --> 00:05:19,250
It just proved to me
once again that there's

68
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:22,166
only so much a driver
alone can really do.

69
00:05:22,250 --> 00:05:25,041
Once I realized this, I knew
I had a lot more to learn.

70
00:05:25,125 --> 00:05:26,916
It might not mean
much to anyone else,

71
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:29,333
but at least I understand it.

72
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:34,166
Takumi's finally woken up!

73
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:37,041
Now this is real progress!

74
00:05:37,125 --> 00:05:38,291
You're not telling lies.

75
00:05:38,375 --> 00:05:40,041
I mean, until everything
went down this summer he

76
00:05:40,125 --> 00:05:43,000
didn't even know the car he
drove was called an Eight-Six.

77
00:05:43,083 --> 00:05:45,208
But after that
magnificent debut on Akina's

78
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:47,458
downhill he kept
winning race after race.

79
00:05:47,541 --> 00:05:49,750
It was like he was
an untouchable giant.

80
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:51,458
And to think of all
we had to go through,

81
00:05:51,541 --> 00:05:52,875
dragging him out to that race.

82
00:05:52,958 --> 00:05:54,916
It was like running across oil.

83
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:55,958
You got that right.

84
00:05:56,041 --> 00:05:57,625
But when I look back on it now.

85
00:05:57,708 --> 00:05:59,125
It is a good memory.

86
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:01,291
Makes me smile.

87
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:06,333
Too bad I never liked battles.

88
00:06:18,041 --> 00:06:21,125
He's not even braking
on the hairpin turn?

89
00:06:24,875 --> 00:06:27,166
What did he just do?

90
00:06:29,750 --> 00:06:31,041
You're telling me
that I don't have

91
00:06:31,125 --> 00:06:34,041
any choice but to
accept the challenges?

92
00:06:34,125 --> 00:06:37,000
I don't think
I like that at all.

93
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:49,500
No way.

94
00:06:49,583 --> 00:06:52,000
He's moving in from the outside?

95
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:54,958
I'm in for any kinda race.

96
00:06:55,041 --> 00:06:57,666
Even a gum tape death match.

97
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:09,000
The less I steer the faster
I can clear those corners.

98
00:07:09,083 --> 00:07:10,333
I don't get it!

99
00:07:10,416 --> 00:07:12,083
I've got the better car
and he's still passing me!

100
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:13,541
Damn!

101
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:16,958
This is my battle tonight
and this is my race,

102
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:19,750
so I'm going to run it my way.

103
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:31,000
We can't win.

104
00:07:31,083 --> 00:07:34,458
We're up against a monster
that outclasses us in every way.

105
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:46,916
He's improving,
one race after another.

106
00:07:56,583 --> 00:07:57,833
Listen...

107
00:07:57,916 --> 00:07:59,875
I don't think I'm a
faster driver than you are.

108
00:07:59,958 --> 00:08:01,291
I really don't.

109
00:08:01,916 --> 00:08:03,916
Look...
Whether you think it or not.

110
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,875
You were the faster driver.

111
00:08:05,958 --> 00:08:07,958
Catch you later.

112
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:17,750
Takumi's getting
better all the time.

113
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:20,625
I don't think I've ever seen
anyone improve as fast as him.

114
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:23,791
He's been one devoted driver
lately, and I can't blame him.

115
00:08:23,875 --> 00:08:26,208
It certainly is paying off.

116
00:08:29,541 --> 00:08:30,583
A white FC.

117
00:08:30,666 --> 00:08:32,416
Check it out!

118
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:36,833
Can I help you, sir?

119
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,166
You sure can.

120
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:41,541
Fill up the tank and
make it high octane.

121
00:08:41,625 --> 00:08:42,875
You got it.

122
00:08:43,458 --> 00:08:44,500
Holy crap.

123
00:08:44,583 --> 00:08:46,208
That's the White Comet of Akagi.

124
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:48,416
Ryosuke Takahashi.

125
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:51,000
Filling it with
high octane, sir.

126
00:08:53,250 --> 00:08:55,500
I have something that I'd
like to talk to you about.

127
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,000
Okay.

128
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:59,625
Do you have any free
time after work tonight?

129
00:08:59,708 --> 00:09:01,208
Sure, but... What's this about?

130
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:02,708
Listen, man.

131
00:09:02,791 --> 00:09:04,958
if you don't have time to
spare today, we can do it later.

132
00:09:05,041 --> 00:09:06,916
No, it's not a problem.

133
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,166
I don't have any plans
once my shift is over.

134
00:09:10,250 --> 00:09:11,500
Sounds great.

135
00:09:11,583 --> 00:09:13,708
Then when you get out of
here, just give me a call.

136
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:15,208
This is my cell number.

137
00:09:15,291 --> 00:09:16,125
Yeah.

138
00:09:16,208 --> 00:09:17,333
Okay.

139
00:09:17,416 --> 00:09:18,291
Cool.

140
00:09:18,375 --> 00:09:20,125
I'll be expecting you.

141
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:26,458
Thank you for your business!

142
00:09:30,958 --> 00:09:32,708
Dude!
What the heck was that?

143
00:09:32,791 --> 00:09:34,166
Ryosuke Takahashi!

144
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:36,916
What was a guy like that
doing here talking to you?

145
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:38,916
I'm not really sure, man.

146
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:40,375
Yeah?

147
00:09:40,458 --> 00:09:42,833
Then maybe you wanna tell me
why you're blushing, dude?

148
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:45,166
I'm not blushing,
it's just, he's who he is,

149
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:47,708
and I'm here in my little
bow tie and tucked in shirt.

150
00:09:47,791 --> 00:09:50,708
I just get nervous when
he's around, okay.

151
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,166
You mean an expeditionary team?

152
00:10:00,250 --> 00:10:02,041
That's what I said.

153
00:10:03,291 --> 00:10:05,916
I want to gather a small
number of highly skilled drivers

154
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,625
from this area and
I want you to take them

155
00:10:07,708 --> 00:10:10,250
to mountain passes
outside this prefecture.

156
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:12,708
Then, you challenge the locals.

157
00:10:12,791 --> 00:10:14,958
If they have a record,
it's your job to break it...

158
00:10:15,041 --> 00:10:16,583
...leave behind
an area legend...

159
00:10:16,666 --> 00:10:18,625
...and then disband.

160
00:10:19,208 --> 00:10:21,875
Unfortunately I don't
have a lot of time left.

161
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:23,166
Maybe a year.

162
00:10:23,250 --> 00:10:25,541
Maybe more, if I'm lucky.

163
00:10:25,916 --> 00:10:27,375
And I gotta be honest with you.

164
00:10:27,458 --> 00:10:30,166
I want to see the end of the
game before that day gets here.

165
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,875
So I'm gonna cut
to the chase, alright?

166
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:34,333
I need your technique.

167
00:10:34,416 --> 00:10:35,750
What?

168
00:10:37,333 --> 00:10:39,666
Would you join my expeditionary
team as one of the drivers?

169
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:41,250
Are you kidding?

170
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:44,791
You're the person who stopped
my consecutive win record.

171
00:10:44,875 --> 00:10:49,541
Now, of course, this is my game,
but if you cooperate with me,

172
00:10:49,625 --> 00:10:52,583
I know I can make it a very
rewarding experience for you.

173
00:10:52,666 --> 00:10:54,166
Rewarding?

174
00:10:54,250 --> 00:10:56,125
Up to now you've
been relying mostly on

175
00:10:56,208 --> 00:10:58,333
your talent and your
senses to guide you.

176
00:10:58,416 --> 00:10:59,666
But before too long...

177
00:10:59,750 --> 00:11:00,875
...you're gonna
run head first into

178
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:02,625
something like a brick wall.

179
00:11:02,708 --> 00:11:04,708
To overcome that
wall, to make it to a

180
00:11:04,791 --> 00:11:06,791
higher level of racing,
you'll need driving skills

181
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,375
that are based on sound theory,

182
00:11:08,458 --> 00:11:10,875
not just the raw instinct
you were born with.

183
00:11:10,958 --> 00:11:12,583
Haven't you begun
to realize you need

184
00:11:12,666 --> 00:11:13,916
more than you're working with?

185
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,125
That if you want
to drive faster,

186
00:11:15,208 --> 00:11:17,666
it's knowledge that's
gonna get you there.

187
00:11:18,041 --> 00:11:21,250
The only reason
I know this is because

188
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:22,750
you're exactly like my brother.

189
00:11:22,833 --> 00:11:25,291
You're the same
type of driver as he is.

190
00:11:25,375 --> 00:11:27,375
Wait, you mean Keisuke?

191
00:11:27,458 --> 00:11:29,333
Out there, when
you have your talent

192
00:11:29,416 --> 00:11:33,083
backed up by some sound theory,
you'll be an unbeatable warrior.

193
00:11:33,166 --> 00:11:35,416
I can teach you everything
that you want to know.

194
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,708
But it's best to learn all of
that in a racing environment.

195
00:11:37,791 --> 00:11:39,000
Not a classroom.

196
00:11:39,083 --> 00:11:41,041
Not standing here.

197
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:43,291
So let's do this together.

198
00:11:43,375 --> 00:11:44,583
You don't have to answer now.

199
00:11:44,666 --> 00:11:46,166
Take some time
to think about it.

200
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:47,166
Just not too long.

201
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:48,875
Okay.

202
00:11:57,166 --> 00:11:59,708
I hope it's a 'yes' kid.

203
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:10,500
What?

204
00:12:11,291 --> 00:12:12,458
Dude!

205
00:12:12,541 --> 00:12:14,083
Ryosuke Takahashi
himself invited you of all

206
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:16,458
people to join his
expeditionary team?

207
00:12:16,541 --> 00:12:18,041
Whoa.

208
00:12:18,125 --> 00:12:19,416
He told me that it's some kind
of special expeditionary team

209
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:21,750
he's putting together to
race outside the prefecture

210
00:12:21,833 --> 00:12:23,625
but itt'l only gonna
last for a year.

211
00:12:23,708 --> 00:12:24,708
That's awesome!

212
00:12:24,791 --> 00:12:25,791
Sweet!

213
00:12:25,875 --> 00:12:27,458
This is the best
news I've ever heard!

214
00:12:27,541 --> 00:12:28,750
I wanna tell Iketani now!

215
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:30,083
I have to!

216
00:12:30,166 --> 00:12:31,916
I can't wait to see the
look the look on his face.

217
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:34,916
Please don't go
stirring up any trouble.

218
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,416
I haven't even decided if
I'm even joining it or not.

219
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:39,000
Dude!

220
00:12:39,083 --> 00:12:40,625
What's there to think about?

221
00:12:40,708 --> 00:12:42,750
Join!

222
00:12:43,125 --> 00:12:44,541
I don't know.

223
00:12:44,625 --> 00:12:46,833
My first battle was just at the
beginning of this summer.

224
00:12:46,916 --> 00:12:49,416
I mean, it hasn't
been six months.

225
00:12:50,125 --> 00:12:52,458
I'm only now getting
interested in cars.

226
00:12:52,541 --> 00:12:54,083
Everything inside
me is wondering

227
00:12:54,166 --> 00:12:56,291
if I even deserve to
be on the team.

228
00:12:56,375 --> 00:12:57,958
Have I earned it?

229
00:12:58,041 --> 00:12:59,458
What is flying
out of your mouth?

230
00:12:59,541 --> 00:13:01,500
You've been driving around,
delivering tofu since you

231
00:13:01,583 --> 00:13:03,125
were in what, the seventh grade?

232
00:13:03,208 --> 00:13:05,041
So I'd say, yeah,
you've earned it.

233
00:13:05,125 --> 00:13:06,833
Cut yourself some slack.

234
00:13:06,916 --> 00:13:08,416
Oh, man.

235
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:10,250
I'd kill to join with you, even
if I was just a gofer, you know.

236
00:13:10,333 --> 00:13:11,833
I'd make coffee runs.

237
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:12,875
Ah, this sucks!

238
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:13,958
Totally sucks!

239
00:13:14,041 --> 00:13:15,458
My rival keeps
pulling farther ahead

240
00:13:15,541 --> 00:13:18,791
and here I am
just standing still!

241
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:20,208
Every since we
talked last night,

242
00:13:20,291 --> 00:13:22,166
I've been pretty confused,
ya know?

243
00:13:22,250 --> 00:13:23,750
I feel like there's
a few things that I

244
00:13:23,833 --> 00:13:25,750
have to do before
I can join the team.

245
00:13:25,833 --> 00:13:29,041
It's the only way I can
do it with a clear head.

246
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:33,791
Killer.

247
00:13:33,875 --> 00:13:35,333
So that's why Ryosuke
wanted to see him?

248
00:13:35,416 --> 00:13:37,541
To invite him onto
a special team?

249
00:13:37,625 --> 00:13:38,958
Yeah.
It's big.

250
00:13:39,041 --> 00:13:40,833
Kinda freaked me out.

251
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:42,250
Well...

252
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:43,916
...he's easily the most
charismatic of the road racers.

253
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,375
No one else comes close.

254
00:13:45,458 --> 00:13:46,958
No one.

255
00:13:47,041 --> 00:13:49,083
And with his record, that guy
is king of the mountain pass.

256
00:13:49,666 --> 00:13:50,791
Then again...

257
00:13:50,875 --> 00:13:52,250
It was Takumi who beat
him on the mountain,

258
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:53,916
so with the two of
them on the same team,

259
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:55,625
you could end up
with something really tight,

260
00:13:55,708 --> 00:13:57,166
or it could blow
up in their faces.

261
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,791
But you never really know.

262
00:13:59,791 --> 00:14:00,791
Hold up.

263
00:14:00,875 --> 00:14:03,166
Y'know, I just
thought of something.

264
00:14:04,875 --> 00:14:07,000
Takumi is considered
the hero of Akina.

265
00:14:07,083 --> 00:14:08,958
The guy could be a
legend if we give him time.

266
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:12,375
Don't you feel like the Red Suns
are stealing him away from us?

267
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:13,875
I mean--

268
00:14:13,958 --> 00:14:14,958
Nah. I think it's a
good idea to support

269
00:14:15,041 --> 00:14:16,625
Takumi in whatever
he chooses to do.

270
00:14:16,708 --> 00:14:18,541
If it makes him a
better driver in the end,

271
00:14:18,625 --> 00:14:20,916
then that's all that really
matters, isn't it?

272
00:14:21,875 --> 00:14:23,708
Think of it like
Takumi's off training

273
00:14:23,791 --> 00:14:26,375
for a year with
Ryosuke Takahashi.

274
00:14:26,708 --> 00:14:28,250
Expeditionary team, huh?

275
00:14:28,333 --> 00:14:30,458
That's a thought he and
I had kicked around before.

276
00:14:30,541 --> 00:14:32,000
It's good training.

277
00:14:32,083 --> 00:14:33,166
I think he should do it.

278
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:34,541
Takumi isn't the
kind of kid who'd

279
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:37,833
be satisfied staying
in Akina forever.

280
00:14:51,916 --> 00:14:54,666
A blown engine
means instant defeat.

281
00:15:36,791 --> 00:15:37,958
Hello?

282
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:40,750
Yeah, it's me.

283
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:42,041
Sorry to bother you with this.

284
00:15:42,125 --> 00:15:43,083
It's got nothing to do with the

285
00:15:43,166 --> 00:15:44,833
stuff we talked
about last night.

286
00:15:44,916 --> 00:15:46,000
I mean, it's not like it's

287
00:15:46,083 --> 00:15:48,208
completely unrelated,
but anyway.

288
00:15:48,291 --> 00:15:49,791
I just...

289
00:15:49,875 --> 00:15:52,791
I wanted to know something, and
I figured you had the answer.

290
00:15:52,875 --> 00:15:54,666
The leader of the Emperor team?

291
00:15:55,375 --> 00:15:57,583
Well, that'd be Kyoichi Sudou.

292
00:15:57,666 --> 00:15:58,916
Okay great.

293
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:01,125
And do you have any idea
where I could find him or

294
00:16:01,208 --> 00:16:03,125
how I could get
in touch with him?

295
00:16:03,208 --> 00:16:04,291
Yeah, of course, I do.

296
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:05,833
Sudou and I go way back.

297
00:16:05,916 --> 00:16:07,625
I can get in touch with
him whenever I need to,

298
00:16:07,708 --> 00:16:09,375
and I can do the same for you.

299
00:16:09,458 --> 00:16:11,000
I, uh...

300
00:16:11,708 --> 00:16:13,791
I really want to
race with him when

301
00:16:13,875 --> 00:16:16,291
the chance comes back around.

302
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:17,250
All right.

303
00:16:17,333 --> 00:16:19,083
And where do you wanna do this?

304
00:16:19,166 --> 00:16:22,291
If it's possible I want to
race on his home turf.

305
00:16:22,375 --> 00:16:24,333
The Iroha Slopes, in Nikko.

306
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:26,750
You can find Sudou there.

307
00:16:27,916 --> 00:16:29,291
I hope you realize
how tough it'll

308
00:16:29,375 --> 00:16:32,166
be to beat him
on his own course.

309
00:16:44,625 --> 00:16:47,875
The kid might be timid but he's
got the instincts of a fighter.

310
00:16:47,958 --> 00:16:51,333
I like the idea of meeting the
enemy on his own grounds.

311
00:16:51,791 --> 00:16:53,666
But above everything
else, he's still gotta be

312
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:56,583
able to drive faster
than the other guy.

313
00:17:04,125 --> 00:17:05,750
Fujiwara Tofu Shop.

314
00:17:05,833 --> 00:17:07,083
What can I do for you?

315
00:17:07,166 --> 00:17:08,875
Hey Mr. F, it's Itsuki.

316
00:17:08,958 --> 00:17:10,958
Oh, you're looking for Takumi.

317
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:12,750
He's not here right now.

318
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:13,750
He's not?

319
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,208
So, then he took
the car with him?

320
00:17:15,291 --> 00:17:16,333
But where'd he go?

321
00:17:16,416 --> 00:17:17,666
Did he say?

322
00:17:18,625 --> 00:17:20,125
Sorry, kid.

323
00:17:20,208 --> 00:17:22,666
I've got no idea.

324
00:17:41,875 --> 00:17:43,916
So this is the Iroha Slopes.

325
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:45,666
I thought it was weird
that there were two roads

326
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:47,458
with the same name on the map.

327
00:17:47,541 --> 00:17:51,916
But now that I'm out here,
wheels to the asphalt, I get it.

328
00:17:53,875 --> 00:17:55,458
Each lane up and
down the mountain is

329
00:17:55,541 --> 00:17:57,375
one way and each
one is separate.

330
00:17:57,458 --> 00:17:59,000
I've never driven
a road like this.

331
00:17:59,083 --> 00:18:01,333
I didn't even know they existed.

332
00:18:17,833 --> 00:18:21,500
This downhill burn
is unbelievable.

333
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:25,333
Dude, was that?

334
00:18:25,416 --> 00:18:26,750
Uh-huh!

335
00:18:27,708 --> 00:18:28,833
What?
Speak up!

336
00:18:28,916 --> 00:18:29,875
I can't hear you!

337
00:18:29,958 --> 00:18:31,375
Dude, check this out.

338
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:35,625
Eight-Six.

339
00:18:35,708 --> 00:18:38,583
Yeah. That's
Ahkina's Eight-Six!

340
00:18:43,416 --> 00:18:45,458
You're screwing with me.

341
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,416
Yeah, alright,
I'll let him know.

342
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:49,541
Kyoichi, it's a
call from the base,

343
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:51,416
they said he's moving fast.

344
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:52,875
He should be up on us soon.

345
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:55,041
They said it's probably him.

346
00:18:59,125 --> 00:19:00,541
Hey, bro.
Can we talk?

347
00:19:00,625 --> 00:19:01,833
Yeah. Sure.

348
00:19:01,916 --> 00:19:02,833
What's up?

349
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:04,291
Someone was kind
enough to tell me

350
00:19:04,375 --> 00:19:07,708
that Akina's Eight-Six was
heading to the Iroha Slopes.

351
00:19:07,791 --> 00:19:08,750
Okay.

352
00:19:08,833 --> 00:19:10,208
Figures.

353
00:19:10,625 --> 00:19:12,000
And you already knew this?

354
00:19:12,083 --> 00:19:13,125
Yeah, sort of.

355
00:19:13,208 --> 00:19:14,708
Is he out for revenge or what?

356
00:19:14,791 --> 00:19:17,416
I mean what is this
all about anyway?

357
00:19:17,500 --> 00:19:18,791
I can't tell.

358
00:19:18,875 --> 00:19:20,000
When I spoke to him about it,
he didn't seem that

359
00:19:20,083 --> 00:19:22,250
concerned about winning
or losing a battle.

360
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:24,375
Must be something, else.

361
00:19:24,750 --> 00:19:26,375
Takumi went to
the Iroha Slopes to

362
00:19:26,458 --> 00:19:28,583
prove something to someone.

363
00:19:37,750 --> 00:19:39,791
Here he comes.

364
00:19:48,458 --> 00:19:51,708
The Eight-Six sounds
different than last time.

365
00:19:52,708 --> 00:19:53,958
A while back...

366
00:19:54,041 --> 00:19:56,583
I heard about this little
shop over in Shibukawa.

367
00:19:56,666 --> 00:19:58,458
Not many people
knew about it at the time,

368
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:00,291
but it had picked up
a very strange engine

369
00:20:00,375 --> 00:20:02,208
from a shall-we-say
'unofficial' source.

370
00:20:02,291 --> 00:20:03,625
Yeah yeah, what
kind of an engine?

371
00:20:03,708 --> 00:20:05,125
Well, it's not
around any longer,

372
00:20:05,208 --> 00:20:06,416
but there used
to be this touring

373
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:08,541
car race category
called Group A.

374
00:20:08,625 --> 00:20:10,791
You ever recall hearing
something like that?

375
00:20:11,291 --> 00:20:14,791
You're telling me that the
Eight-Six has a Group A engine?

376
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,291
More than likely.

377
00:20:16,375 --> 00:20:18,708
If it's an engine built by
TRD, which was in

378
00:20:18,791 --> 00:20:21,041
the AE-101 of Group A,

379
00:20:21,125 --> 00:20:23,791
then it can produce
two hundred forty hp.

380
00:20:23,875 --> 00:20:26,500
At above eleven thousand
rpm out of its one point

381
00:20:26,583 --> 00:20:29,333
six liter Natural
Aspiration engine.

382
00:20:29,416 --> 00:20:31,500
This is an ultra high
performance engine.

383
00:20:31,583 --> 00:20:33,541
It's been detuned
for street use and sits

384
00:20:33,625 --> 00:20:35,916
under the hood
of Akina's Eight-Six.

385
00:20:36,416 --> 00:20:37,666
Whatever...

386
00:20:37,750 --> 00:20:39,375
It's not like it matters
it's a racing engine now.

387
00:20:39,458 --> 00:20:41,458
It's still a one
point six liter NA.

388
00:20:41,541 --> 00:20:42,708
It has its limitations.

389
00:20:42,791 --> 00:20:44,166
It's not magical.

390
00:20:44,250 --> 00:20:45,750
That's true.

391
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:49,333
So you fixed the Eight-Six?

392
00:20:49,416 --> 00:20:50,208
We did.

393
00:20:50,291 --> 00:20:51,500
I hope I don't have to remind

394
00:20:51,583 --> 00:20:53,291
you what I said back in Akagi.

395
00:20:53,375 --> 00:20:54,750
I told you I'd put off the match

396
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:56,750
between us until you
got a better car.

397
00:20:56,833 --> 00:20:58,791
One that could actually compete.

398
00:20:58,875 --> 00:21:01,166
That looks like the
same one from before.

399
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:04,125
It might look like it but this
isn't the same car at all.

400
00:21:04,208 --> 00:21:05,333
If you ask me this is a much

401
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:07,208
better car than the
one you raced.

402
00:21:07,291 --> 00:21:08,291
So what do ya say?

403
00:21:08,375 --> 00:21:10,208
Will this do the job?

404
00:21:12,875 --> 00:21:14,416
I'm always
interested in settling

405
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:16,583
an unfinished battle, so yeah.

406
00:21:16,666 --> 00:21:18,833
We'll get this taken
care of right now.

407
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:19,958
Good point.

408
00:21:20,041 --> 00:21:22,000
But what interests
me isn't the power.

409
00:21:22,458 --> 00:21:24,083
it's the cornering.

410
00:21:25,125 --> 00:21:27,208
The sporting ability
will improve drastically

411
00:21:27,291 --> 00:21:29,000
with the installation
of that engine.

412
00:21:29,083 --> 00:21:30,875
And the potentially
superior cornering

413
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:33,041
performance could
be even more refined.

414
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:36,166
The levels to which this
will take the sport stagger me.

415
00:21:36,750 --> 00:21:38,500
With the right
combinations of genius

416
00:21:38,583 --> 00:21:42,458
and luck it could even equal
Kyo-eechi's misfiring system.

417
00:21:51,291 --> 00:21:52,916
This is a one
round, downhill match.

418
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,750
Once we get down to
the base of the mountain.

419
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:56,125
You're gonna see three bridges.

420
00:21:56,208 --> 00:21:58,083
The goal is at the
end of the third bridge.

421
00:21:58,166 --> 00:21:59,708
You make it
there first, you win.

422
00:21:59,791 --> 00:22:01,166
Is that simple enough?

423
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:02,125
You go ahead.

424
00:22:02,208 --> 00:22:04,083
I'll follow.

425
00:22:04,791 --> 00:22:06,458
If you maintain
your lead til you

426
00:22:06,541 --> 00:22:08,750
cross that finish line,
you'll be the winner.

427
00:22:08,833 --> 00:22:10,500
I pass you, I win.

428
00:22:10,583 --> 00:22:11,791
That cool by you?

429
00:22:11,875 --> 00:22:14,208
That's not fair.

430
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:16,125
If you think I'm
putting myself at a

431
00:22:16,208 --> 00:22:18,083
disadvantage by letting
you slide in front,

432
00:22:18,166 --> 00:22:19,708
then you're insulting me.

433
00:22:19,791 --> 00:22:21,500
The Iroha Slopes
are my home course

434
00:22:21,583 --> 00:22:23,750
and you'd do best to
not forget that.

435
00:22:23,833 --> 00:22:26,583
It'd be a slaughter out there
unless I gave you a handicap.

436
00:22:26,666 --> 00:22:28,791
You want this to be fair, right?

437
00:22:28,875 --> 00:22:32,291
After this is over we can
argue about it all you want.

438
00:22:32,375 --> 00:22:33,958
Let's go.

439
00:22:39,708 --> 00:22:41,833
The Iroha Slopes
downhill is laid out

440
00:22:41,916 --> 00:22:45,041
like an autocross course
if it had a steep slope.

441
00:22:45,750 --> 00:22:48,083
No one can defeat Kyoichi.

442
00:22:49,250 --> 00:22:50,958
He learned his
technique in autocross,

443
00:22:51,041 --> 00:22:54,625
which made him the master
of slow speed corners.

444
00:23:24,916 --> 00:23:26,083
I see it now.

445
00:23:26,166 --> 00:23:27,958
The car is running
a little faster.

446
00:23:28,041 --> 00:23:30,125
It's not like a turbo,
it has the acceleration

447
00:23:30,208 --> 00:23:31,875
of a mechanically tuned car.

448
00:23:31,958 --> 00:23:33,333
But it doesn't
matter how you tune it...

449
00:23:33,416 --> 00:23:35,291
It's still just a
little Eight-Six.

450
00:23:35,375 --> 00:23:38,583
And I've got three
hundred and fifty HP.

451
00:24:08,916 --> 00:24:11,666
That's some unbelievable
high rev on that engine.

452
00:24:11,750 --> 00:24:13,250
Badass attitude.

453
00:24:13,333 --> 00:24:14,958
You really think you can
hold your own against my

454
00:24:15,041 --> 00:24:18,541
misfiring system with those
kinda back alley tricks?

455
00:24:37,958 --> 00:24:40,166
Not like it matters what
kinda car I'm up against,

456
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:42,458
there's no way I
can lose on this run.

457
00:24:42,541 --> 00:24:47,041
Just like Ryosuke rules in
Akagi, I'm the emperor here.

458
00:24:47,541 --> 00:24:49,791
I always get what I want!

459
00:24:57,416 --> 00:24:58,833
Man, he's right on my bumper.

460
00:24:58,916 --> 00:25:02,416
I'll have to go at it harder
if I'm gonna pull this off.

461
00:25:06,791 --> 00:25:08,625
The slope's about
to level out on him.

462
00:25:08,708 --> 00:25:11,000
His Eight-Six is
gonna lose some speed.

463
00:25:11,083 --> 00:25:12,583
When that happens,
he'll be stuck right in

464
00:25:12,666 --> 00:25:15,958
the crosshairs of
my counterattack.

465
00:25:23,666 --> 00:25:25,250
The biggest pitfall
of this course

466
00:25:25,333 --> 00:25:27,125
is that once you've driven
through the slow corners,

467
00:25:27,208 --> 00:25:28,958
your senses have
trouble readjusting

468
00:25:29,041 --> 00:25:30,375
to the high-speed corners.

469
00:25:30,458 --> 00:25:32,458
It's the kind of
optical shift that'll trip up

470
00:25:32,541 --> 00:25:34,666
even the most
experienced road racers.

471
00:25:34,750 --> 00:25:36,458
And while it might just
be a natural reaction,

472
00:25:36,541 --> 00:25:38,416
in the right hands,
it can be manipulated

473
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:40,041
as an excellent technique.

474
00:25:40,125 --> 00:25:43,125
No one can switch to the
high-speed mode there.

475
00:25:45,541 --> 00:25:48,250
No one that is,
except one person.

476
00:25:48,333 --> 00:25:51,916
The White Comet of Akagi,
Ryosuke Takahashi.

477
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:54,333
He's the one.

478
00:26:06,916 --> 00:26:08,250
A bridge!

479
00:26:08,333 --> 00:26:09,916
The goal is up ahead!

480
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,750
The steep slope ends
just before the first bridge.

481
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:14,875
You're gonna need
some real power now.

482
00:26:14,958 --> 00:26:17,625
'Cuz Kyoichi Sudou is about
to blow the doors off that

483
00:26:17,708 --> 00:26:19,625
Eight-Six of yours
and make you regret you

484
00:26:19,708 --> 00:26:22,750
ever came back
asking for seconds.

485
00:26:42,000 --> 00:26:43,375
The second bridge.

486
00:26:43,458 --> 00:26:45,458
The right bend fires
you out like a bullet--

487
00:26:45,541 --> 00:26:47,541
a scary feeling
after having gotten used to

488
00:26:47,625 --> 00:26:49,416
the slow speed section before.

489
00:26:49,500 --> 00:26:51,875
It's gotta be jarring for
someone who's never done it.

490
00:26:51,958 --> 00:26:53,958
And then there's an optical
illusion on the bend,

491
00:26:54,041 --> 00:26:56,083
making the road
look narrower than it is.

492
00:26:56,166 --> 00:26:58,208
Like you can't approach
the outside enough.

493
00:26:58,291 --> 00:27:01,458
So I just poke my
nose out a bit, and...

494
00:27:01,541 --> 00:27:04,291
This match is mine.

495
00:27:07,666 --> 00:27:08,875
The third bridge.

496
00:27:08,958 --> 00:27:10,666
The inside and outside positions

497
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:12,125
will be reversed on the bridge.

498
00:27:12,208 --> 00:27:14,583
It's my trademark finish.

499
00:27:14,666 --> 00:27:18,833
Once we're driving side by side,
this whole thing'll be over.

500
00:27:18,916 --> 00:27:19,666
There it is!

501
00:27:19,750 --> 00:27:20,625
Should I do it?

502
00:27:20,708 --> 00:27:22,375
Go!

503
00:27:23,291 --> 00:27:24,583
You gotta death wish?

504
00:27:24,666 --> 00:27:25,958
You're going too fast!

505
00:27:26,041 --> 00:27:27,750
You can't turn at that speed!

506
00:27:27,833 --> 00:27:28,791
Come on.

507
00:27:28,875 --> 00:27:30,583
Turn, Eight-Six,
you can do it, baby.

508
00:27:30,666 --> 00:27:32,333
Turn!

509
00:27:32,416 --> 00:27:35,375
I don't know if I can hold it!

510
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:48,416
The key point in the battle
is the switch in positions

511
00:27:48,500 --> 00:27:51,041
during that left bend
before the third bridge.

512
00:27:51,375 --> 00:27:54,458
No way an ordinary Eight-Six
coulda make that turn.

513
00:27:54,541 --> 00:27:56,166
And there's no way
in hell a driver with

514
00:27:56,250 --> 00:27:59,291
normal senses
would dive into it.

515
00:27:59,375 --> 00:28:01,375
Were you positive it would work?

516
00:28:01,458 --> 00:28:02,458
Yeah.

517
00:28:02,541 --> 00:28:04,541
I usually see it first.

518
