00:51:34,083 --> 00:51:36,208
back pocket that's
gonna blindside Takumi

1031
00:51:36,291 --> 00:51:37,500
at just the wrong time.

1032
00:51:37,583 --> 00:51:39,416
But Takumi's father
defeated Kai's father

1033
00:51:39,500 --> 00:51:41,541
on this same mountain pass
when they were younger,

1034
00:51:41,625 --> 00:51:42,291
isn't that right?

1035
00:51:42,375 --> 00:51:43,500
Yeah.

1036
00:51:43,583 --> 00:51:44,833
Takumi mumbled something
about his dad giving

1037
00:51:44,916 --> 00:51:47,250
him some advice but that
it didn't make any sense.

1038
00:51:47,333 --> 00:51:48,541
So who knows.

1039
00:51:48,625 --> 00:51:51,500
I have a bad feeling
he's in trouble up there.

1040
00:51:51,583 --> 00:51:54,750
I just hope he makes
it down in one piece.

1041
00:52:01,416 --> 00:52:03,708
Leaves are blowing everywhere
and thanks to the wind,

1042
00:52:03,791 --> 00:52:05,958
there are piles of
them scattered all over.

1043
00:52:06,041 --> 00:52:07,500
This is tough.

1044
00:52:07,583 --> 00:52:10,250
If I roll over even one of them
I'll lose control of my car.

1045
00:52:10,333 --> 00:52:12,166
But since the Eight-Six
is in front of me this'll be

1046
00:52:12,250 --> 00:52:13,916
even more of an issue for him.

1047
00:52:14,000 --> 00:52:16,666
He has no idea
when he's gonna skid.

1048
00:52:21,916 --> 00:52:23,833
It's so hard to drive tonight.

1049
00:52:23,916 --> 00:52:26,458
I'm better off letting
the car drift itself.

1050
00:52:27,458 --> 00:52:29,083
I just gotta skid
the back wheels early

1051
00:52:29,166 --> 00:52:31,541
and then let all
four of 'em drift.

1052
00:52:32,541 --> 00:52:34,791
Wait.
What's that idiot doing?

1053
00:52:34,875 --> 00:52:36,500
No wonder he's
shooting for the leaves.

1054
00:52:36,583 --> 00:52:39,500
A sloppy street
is easier to drift on.

1055
00:52:42,458 --> 00:52:44,875
You're a tough driver
Takumi, but a cheap trick

1056
00:52:44,958 --> 00:52:47,416
like that isn't
gonna work on me.

1057
00:52:47,500 --> 00:52:49,500
Sometimes the lines
you need to follow

1058
00:52:49,583 --> 00:52:53,125
are inside the inner shoulder
on the Iroha Slopes.

1059
00:52:53,208 --> 00:52:54,458
If this is going to work.

1060
00:52:54,541 --> 00:52:57,041
the timing is
absolutely crucial.

1061
00:52:58,250 --> 00:53:00,583
We're at corner
number thirty-three.

1062
00:53:00,666 --> 00:53:02,083
I can hear them.

1063
00:53:02,166 --> 00:53:03,791
And it sounds like they'll be
on the hairpin any second.

1064
00:53:03,875 --> 00:53:04,916
Yeah, all right.

1065
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:07,250
Just call me back
when they get there.

1066
00:53:07,333 --> 00:53:08,833
It's about to get interesting.

1067
00:53:08,916 --> 00:53:10,333
What?

1068
00:53:12,125 --> 00:53:13,583
I have a bad feeling.

1069
00:53:13,666 --> 00:53:16,041
I don't know what it is, but
he's going to pull something.

1070
00:53:16,125 --> 00:53:18,500
Maybe something dangerous.

1071
00:53:25,375 --> 00:53:26,833
I can't wait any longer, Pop.

1072
00:53:26,916 --> 00:53:28,791
It's now or never.

1073
00:53:30,083 --> 00:53:32,708
Man, I can't shake
this feeling in my gut.

1074
00:53:32,791 --> 00:53:34,708
Somethings going down.

1075
00:53:35,291 --> 00:53:36,333
Okay.
Here it goes!

1076
00:53:36,416 --> 00:53:38,958
I'll attack him in
corner thirty three!

1077
00:53:39,916 --> 00:53:40,458
Hey!

1078
00:53:40,541 --> 00:53:42,000
Here they are!

1079
00:53:44,875 --> 00:53:46,833
I see 'em!
The Eight-Six is in front!

1080
00:53:46,916 --> 00:53:48,333
Here I go!

1081
00:53:53,000 --> 00:53:54,166
What?
What's going on?

1082
00:53:54,250 --> 00:53:56,083
Are you trying to
tell me that the SW

1083
00:53:56,166 --> 00:53:57,750
took the inside
of the inner line?

1084
00:53:57,833 --> 00:53:58,791
He did?

1085
00:53:58,875 --> 00:54:00,708
He actually
passed the Eight Six?

1086
00:54:00,791 --> 00:54:02,375
He already got passed?

1087
00:54:02,458 --> 00:54:03,625
Home court advantage.

1088
00:54:03,708 --> 00:54:04,625
Huh...

1089
00:54:04,708 --> 00:54:05,708
Well...

1090
00:54:05,791 --> 00:54:07,208
...you did it, Kai.

1091
00:54:07,291 --> 00:54:08,291
Serious?

1092
00:54:08,375 --> 00:54:10,083
The SW already
passed the Eight-Six?

1093
00:54:10,166 --> 00:54:11,916
And he pulled it off
in corner thirty three?

1094
00:54:12,000 --> 00:54:14,000
These two are really
kicking up the heat tonight!

1095
00:54:14,083 --> 00:54:15,041
That's a hairpin turn.

1096
00:54:15,125 --> 00:54:16,250
How'd he get through?

1097
00:54:16,333 --> 00:54:17,500
Did you guys hear that?

1098
00:54:17,583 --> 00:54:19,416
This is no easy race.

1099
00:54:19,500 --> 00:54:22,166
Come on, Takumi!
You can do this!!

1100
00:54:55,375 --> 00:54:57,041
Sorry about the
surprise there pal,

1101
00:54:57,125 --> 00:54:58,625
but the line
inside the inner shoulder

1102
00:54:58,708 --> 00:55:00,500
is in the air,
not on the ground.

1103
00:55:00,583 --> 00:55:03,583
The hairpins up here on the
Slopes have a big height gap.

1104
00:55:03,666 --> 00:55:05,791
Sure, some people
might call this cheating.

1105
00:55:05,875 --> 00:55:08,916
But it's what we
locals call victory.

1106
00:55:10,375 --> 00:55:12,750
I got this in the bag!

1107
00:55:17,125 --> 00:55:19,625
If this keeps up,
I'm gonna lose!

1108
00:55:26,666 --> 00:55:28,208
So whattya think, bro?

1109
00:55:28,291 --> 00:55:29,208
Hard to say.

1110
00:55:29,291 --> 00:55:30,666
Eleven hairpins left.

1111
00:55:30,750 --> 00:55:32,833
At this point
it's anyone's match.

1112
00:55:33,166 --> 00:55:35,500
What do you mean
by that, Ryosuke?

1113
00:55:35,583 --> 00:55:37,416
So far the race is turning out

1114
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:39,041
about the way you
thought it would.

1115
00:55:39,125 --> 00:55:41,208
But don't you think
your guy made his move

1116
00:55:41,291 --> 00:55:42,916
just a bit too early?

1117
00:55:43,000 --> 00:55:44,750
Making your moves
early in the run like

1118
00:55:44,833 --> 00:55:46,583
that gives your opponent
time to recover

1119
00:55:46,666 --> 00:55:49,000
from the shock
of it and compensate.

1120
00:55:49,708 --> 00:55:50,875
We're at corner thirty seven.

1121
00:55:50,958 --> 00:55:52,833
I can see 'em now!

1122
00:55:55,208 --> 00:55:58,416
At this rate the gap's
gonna widen even more.

1123
00:56:03,666 --> 00:56:05,166
This guy's good.

1124
00:56:05,250 --> 00:56:08,208
I better pull the stunt again if
I'm gonna get him off my bumper.

1125
00:56:09,541 --> 00:56:10,500
Dude!

1126
00:56:10,583 --> 00:56:12,125
He jumped!

1127
00:56:12,625 --> 00:56:14,208
Go!

1128
00:56:32,583 --> 00:56:34,916
He managed the
jump on his first try?

1129
00:56:35,000 --> 00:56:36,166
Man...

1130
00:56:36,250 --> 00:56:37,208
He might have all the
gut reactions and the

1131
00:56:37,291 --> 00:56:38,583
talent of a
mountain pass driver,

1132
00:56:38,666 --> 00:56:40,750
but once he let me get in
front of him his chance

1133
00:56:40,833 --> 00:56:43,041
at winning slipped
right through his fingers.

1134
00:56:43,125 --> 00:56:45,791
I'll keep this pace
until the goal.

1135
00:56:54,833 --> 00:56:57,541
Wait, the line can't be
blocked no matter what?

1136
00:56:59,291 --> 00:57:00,083
Nope.

1137
00:57:00,166 --> 00:57:01,291
And you send Takumi out there

1138
00:57:01,375 --> 00:57:03,250
without even
telling him about it?

1139
00:57:03,958 --> 00:57:05,500
When you go down
the Iroha Slopes

1140
00:57:05,583 --> 00:57:06,916
there are bridges and a tunnel.

1141
00:57:07,000 --> 00:57:07,708
Remember?

1142
00:57:07,791 --> 00:57:09,000
Of course.

1143
00:57:09,083 --> 00:57:10,541
What I did tell the
kid was that his only shot

1144
00:57:10,625 --> 00:57:11,958
at overtaking his
opponent would be

1145
00:57:12,041 --> 00:57:13,916
at the last point on the course.

1146
00:57:14,708 --> 00:57:16,541
I also told him that
no matter what he did

1147
00:57:16,625 --> 00:57:19,458
at that point in the race
he'd be trailing the other car.

1148
00:57:19,541 --> 00:57:21,166
He didn't understand
it at the time,

1149
00:57:21,250 --> 00:57:22,500
but he's a sharp kid,

1150
00:57:22,583 --> 00:57:25,000
so there's a chance
he's figured it out by now.

1151
00:57:25,083 --> 00:57:27,333
You gave him some advice
on how to pass, right?

1152
00:57:27,416 --> 00:57:29,375
Sort of, I guess.

1153
00:57:30,625 --> 00:57:34,000
If he understands everything
I was saying to him...

1154
00:57:35,041 --> 00:57:36,750
Then he's got about
a fifty-fifty shot

1155
00:57:36,833 --> 00:57:38,833
of edging out the other
kid before the finish.

1156
00:57:38,916 --> 00:57:40,250
That's all?

1157
00:57:40,333 --> 00:57:43,083
Your own son and you're
calling the odds at fifty-fifty?

1158
00:57:43,166 --> 00:57:44,875
That is low.

1159
00:57:45,291 --> 00:57:46,541
Maybe so...

1160
00:57:46,625 --> 00:57:49,500
I at least wanted to
challenge the kid a little.

1161
00:57:55,416 --> 00:57:59,666
Bunta, this time you're going to
be the one on the losing end.

1162
00:58:12,916 --> 00:58:14,666
He's unbelievable in that car.

1163
00:58:14,750 --> 00:58:16,750
It's even more
obvious from behind.

1164
00:58:16,833 --> 00:58:19,041
We're almost at the same
skill level on the straightaway,

1165
00:58:19,125 --> 00:58:22,541
but he's so much
faster in these corners.

1166
00:58:24,666 --> 00:58:26,541
I'm breaking
myself just to keep up.

1167
00:58:26,625 --> 00:58:28,625
How can I blow
past him like this?

1168
00:58:28,708 --> 00:58:30,166
Forget it.
It's no use.

1169
00:58:30,250 --> 00:58:32,500
I'm gonna lose
just like dad said.

1170
00:58:33,458 --> 00:58:34,875
Wait a minute.

1171
00:58:34,958 --> 00:58:37,458
What was it he was
trying to tell me again?

1172
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:41,250
Your best shot at passing is

1173
00:58:41,333 --> 00:58:43,208
going to be on
the very last bridge.

1174
00:58:43,291 --> 00:58:45,041
That's when your opponent
will be ahead of you,

1175
00:58:45,125 --> 00:58:46,541
so try and watch for it.

1176
00:58:46,625 --> 00:58:48,833
But, you don't know
he's gonna be ahead.

1177
00:58:48,916 --> 00:58:51,250
You better believe I do.

1178
00:58:51,333 --> 00:58:53,166
Now this is important,
so listen up.

1179
00:58:53,250 --> 00:58:55,208
I'll only say it once.

1180
00:58:56,708 --> 00:58:58,541
Dry leaves start
to accumulate on the

1181
00:58:58,625 --> 00:59:00,458
Iroha Slopes this
time of the year.

1182
00:59:00,541 --> 00:59:03,166
Those dry leaves
might decide the winner.

1183
00:59:03,750 --> 00:59:05,666
Once you poke your nose
in on the first bridge,

1184
00:59:05,750 --> 00:59:08,333
there's just enough room for
two cars to enter the second,

1185
00:59:08,416 --> 00:59:10,958
but it'll be a pretty
tight squeeze.

1186
00:59:11,291 --> 00:59:14,166
I know you have the technique
to stay right beside him.

1187
00:59:14,750 --> 00:59:17,666
You'll be tangled up
entering that third bridge.

1188
00:59:18,750 --> 00:59:21,000
Luck'll do the rest.

1189
00:59:21,083 --> 00:59:23,416
Do your best, kid.

1190
00:59:30,458 --> 00:59:33,125
So dad knew that Kai was
gonna use the jump up here.

1191
00:59:33,208 --> 00:59:35,208
He knew how all
of this would go down.

1192
00:59:35,291 --> 00:59:38,166
But now I don't know
what move to make next.

1193
00:59:38,250 --> 00:59:40,750
These dry leaves are stacking
up all over the place.

1194
00:59:40,833 --> 00:59:42,958
What am I gonna do?

1195
00:59:46,500 --> 00:59:47,333
One more left.

1196
00:59:47,416 --> 00:59:49,041
The last hairpin turn.

1197
00:59:49,125 --> 00:59:50,833
And even if he can get
out of his middle gear

1198
00:59:50,916 --> 00:59:52,916
fast enough off the
curve he still won't

1199
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:55,041
be able to catch up with me.

1200
01:00:00,875 --> 01:00:02,333
I'm feeling good, Pop.

1201
01:00:02,416 --> 01:00:05,625
Everything is going
just as we planned.

1202
01:00:08,500 --> 01:00:09,416
I can see
the edge of the

1203
01:00:09,500 --> 01:00:11,750
asphalt through
the dried leaves.

1204
01:00:12,208 --> 01:00:13,208
That's what he meant!

1205
01:00:13,291 --> 01:00:16,000
I got it!
I know what I have to do!

1206
01:00:19,083 --> 01:00:19,791
Here it goes!

1207
01:00:19,875 --> 01:00:22,000
This is my
last chance!

1208
01:00:29,916 --> 01:00:31,958
How is he passing
me on the inside!

1209
01:00:32,041 --> 01:00:34,291
That isn't possible!

1210
01:00:37,666 --> 01:00:39,125
What just happened back there?

1211
01:00:39,208 --> 01:00:41,125
What the hell was that?!

1212
01:00:47,333 --> 01:00:48,083
Here they come!

1213
01:00:48,166 --> 01:00:49,625
Who's leading?

1214
01:00:51,041 --> 01:00:52,666
Looks like they're
running side by side!

1215
01:00:52,750 --> 01:00:54,041
Whoa!

1216
01:00:54,125 --> 01:00:55,125
If either of them moves
an inch, they'll both slam

1217
01:00:55,208 --> 01:00:57,791
into the concrete walls
on the bridge!

1218
01:01:40,875 --> 01:01:42,166
I lost.

1219
01:01:42,250 --> 01:01:43,791
I can't believe a
local was beaten

1220
01:01:43,875 --> 01:01:46,083
because of falling leaves.

1221
01:01:46,625 --> 01:01:49,958
You're one hell of a
driver Takumi Fujiwara.

1222
01:01:50,041 --> 01:01:51,708
The Eight-Six pulled it off.

1223
01:01:51,791 --> 01:01:53,666
Kai spun out right
before the finish line

1224
01:01:53,750 --> 01:01:56,083
and didn't even cross it.

1225
01:01:56,166 --> 01:01:57,250
Too bad.

1226
01:01:57,333 --> 01:01:58,791
Good call.

1227
01:02:00,208 --> 01:02:01,625
It's time for us to clear out.

1228
01:02:01,708 --> 01:02:03,208
Don't you think?

1229
01:02:03,583 --> 01:02:05,000
You got it.

1230
01:02:06,500 --> 01:02:09,666
Takumi Fujiwara's
gonna be big someday.

1231
01:02:09,750 --> 01:02:13,333
So big there's no chance
he'll stay in the Gunma area.

1232
01:02:13,416 --> 01:02:17,083
I understand why Ryosuke
sees so much promise in him.

1233
01:02:17,166 --> 01:02:22,166
In fact, one day, he's gonna
leave Ryosuke far behind him.

1234
01:02:22,250 --> 01:02:24,000
Right on, we're gonna
hit the road too.

1235
01:02:24,083 --> 01:02:24,875
Cool.

1236
01:02:24,958 --> 01:02:26,250
Hey, sounds like it's over guys.

1237
01:02:26,333 --> 01:02:27,791
The Eight-Six won it.

1238
01:02:28,416 --> 01:02:31,333
He did it!
My best friend is so cool!

1239
01:02:31,416 --> 01:02:33,208
I can't believe I got to
be here here when the

1240
01:02:33,291 --> 01:02:35,625
new legend of
the Eight-Six began.

1241
01:02:36,000 --> 01:02:37,125
I love that car.

1242
01:02:37,208 --> 01:02:38,708
It's awesome.

1243
01:02:38,791 --> 01:02:40,958
You know you don't
really need to cry about this.

1244
01:02:41,041 --> 01:02:42,875
I'm just so happy for him!

1245
01:02:42,958 --> 01:02:44,666
I can't keep
from crying, either!

1246
01:02:44,750 --> 01:02:48,250
He won, he won,
I can't believe he won!

1247
01:02:53,541 --> 01:02:56,416
Hey, thanks a lot for
dodging me at the end there.

1248
01:02:56,500 --> 01:02:58,458
You could have
split my car in two.

1249
01:02:58,833 --> 01:02:59,958
And it's not even my car.

1250
01:03:00,041 --> 01:03:01,916
It belongs to my dad.

1251
01:03:02,000 --> 01:03:04,625
I wanted to return it to
him in good condition.

1252
01:03:04,708 --> 01:03:05,875
Yeah, I know what you mean.

1253
01:03:05,958 --> 01:03:07,583
Same here.

1254
01:03:07,666 --> 01:03:09,083
I was driving around
the other day and I

1255
01:03:09,166 --> 01:03:11,208
passed the Eight Six
over on Akina.

1256
01:03:11,291 --> 01:03:14,125
Guess it stuck in my head,
because ever since that time,

1257
01:03:14,208 --> 01:03:17,291
I thought there was no way I
could ever best it in a race.

1258
01:03:17,375 --> 01:03:18,458
It didn't matter that I knew

1259
01:03:18,541 --> 01:03:20,875
I wasn't racing
against your father.

1260
01:03:21,333 --> 01:03:22,541
That was one hell of a run.

1261
01:03:22,625 --> 01:03:24,333
And now that I'm sitting
in the loser's corner,

1262
01:03:24,416 --> 01:03:27,125
hindsight being what it is, I
guess my premonition was right.

1263
01:03:27,208 --> 01:03:29,750
Maybe I couldn't beat you, but
it was a good experience for me.

1264
01:03:29,833 --> 01:03:31,583
It's a shock for me to
lose on my own turf,

1265
01:03:31,666 --> 01:03:33,166
but I'll prob'ly
think back on this as

1266
01:03:33,250 --> 01:03:35,000
one of those life
changing moments.

1267
01:03:35,083 --> 01:03:37,375
You and your dad
are both pretty great.

1268
01:03:37,458 --> 01:03:39,333
We're doing this
again someday, you know.

1269
01:03:39,416 --> 01:03:41,833
And I'll train every
day til then.

1270
01:03:41,916 --> 01:03:43,208
See ya.

1271
01:04:05,416 --> 01:04:07,083
Geez, it's freezing
out here today!

1272
01:04:07,166 --> 01:04:08,958
Takumi, do you have a pocket
warmer I could borrow?

1273
01:04:09,041 --> 01:04:10,500
Or maybe a torch?

1274
01:04:10,583 --> 01:04:11,250
Nope.

1275
01:04:11,333 --> 01:04:12,583
Sorry man, I don't.

1276
01:04:12,666 --> 01:04:15,250
I hate the cold weather.

1277
01:04:16,958 --> 01:04:18,416
So.

1278
01:04:18,500 --> 01:04:19,541
Hey.

1279
01:04:20,791 --> 01:04:23,208
What do you plan on
doing after graduation?

1280
01:04:23,291 --> 01:04:24,916
Graduation huh...

1281
01:04:25,000 --> 01:04:26,958
Right, dude.
After you graduate.

1282
01:04:27,041 --> 01:04:28,750
You're going to
college, aren't you?

1283
01:04:28,833 --> 01:04:29,875
Nope.

1284
01:04:29,958 --> 01:04:32,041
Not even a vocational school?

1285
01:04:32,125 --> 01:04:33,333
I don't know.

1286
01:04:33,416 --> 01:04:34,666
Well, if you haven't decided,

1287
01:04:34,750 --> 01:04:36,250
why don't you apply
here as a full-timer?

1288
01:04:36,333 --> 01:04:38,458
Do you know how much fun the
two of us could have together?

1289
01:04:38,541 --> 01:04:39,875
You're joking.

1290
01:04:40,791 --> 01:04:43,166
No. I'm asking for a full
time spot starting in April.

1291
01:04:43,250 --> 01:04:44,708
It seems like the
next best step for me.

1292
01:04:44,791 --> 01:04:46,916
And I couldn't think
of anything else to do.

1293
01:04:47,291 --> 01:04:49,541
Dude, why don't you ask him too?

1294
01:04:50,666 --> 01:04:52,791
Man, this hesitation
thing you got going

1295
01:04:52,875 --> 01:04:55,541
on is a tremendous time waster.

1296
01:04:58,208 --> 01:05:00,250
See you guys tomorrow.

1297
01:05:10,208 --> 01:05:11,791
Your car's different isn't it?

1298
01:05:11,875 --> 01:05:14,750
Your seat, the feeling
of the car when it drives.

1299
01:05:14,833 --> 01:05:17,875
I dunno, it just feels
different from before.

1300
01:05:19,416 --> 01:05:20,916
So Takumi...

1301
01:05:21,000 --> 01:05:23,458
Do you have any plans
for Christmas this year?

1302
01:05:23,541 --> 01:05:24,916
I don't know.

1303
01:05:25,541 --> 01:05:28,583
Well, does your family usually
have a party or a dinner?

1304
01:05:28,666 --> 01:05:30,041
We haven't done much
around my house

1305
01:05:30,125 --> 01:05:31,250
for Christmas since I was a kid.

1306
01:05:31,333 --> 01:05:33,166
To us it's just
like another day.

1307
01:05:33,250 --> 01:05:36,250
Maybe since I don't have
a mom, we just let it go.

1308
01:05:37,416 --> 01:05:39,291
But anyway, enough about that.

1309
01:05:39,375 --> 01:05:42,166
So what is you've been
wanting to talk to me about?

1310
01:05:42,250 --> 01:05:43,625
I wanted you to know.

1311
01:05:43,708 --> 01:05:46,041
I broke up with the guy who
drives that Mercedes Benz.

1312
01:05:46,583 --> 01:05:48,791
Look, whoever you wanna date is
none of my business okay?

1313
01:05:48,875 --> 01:05:50,583
You are a terrible liar.

1314
01:05:50,666 --> 01:05:52,166
If you thought it was
none of your business,

1315
01:05:52,250 --> 01:05:55,375
you woudn't keep ignoring me
every time you saw me.

1316
01:05:55,458 --> 01:05:57,458
Because you were already
involved, you ignore me.

1317
01:05:57,541 --> 01:05:59,083
Simple man math.

1318
01:05:59,583 --> 01:06:01,625
We went to the beach over
the summer and we kissed.

1319
01:06:01,708 --> 01:06:03,125
You're mad 'cause you
think what I've done

1320
01:06:03,208 --> 01:06:04,708
since then was a betrayal.

1321
01:06:04,791 --> 01:06:06,833
Isn't that what
this is all about?

1322
01:06:08,666 --> 01:06:10,208
I'm sorry.

1323
01:06:22,208 --> 01:06:23,625
It's cold.

1324
01:06:24,000 --> 01:06:25,625
Winter is coming.

1325
01:06:25,708 --> 01:06:27,708
I can't tell how you
feel about all of this,

1326
01:06:27,791 --> 01:06:30,291
but I really want to be
your friend again, Takumi.

1327
01:06:30,375 --> 01:06:31,916
I can't do that.

1328
01:06:32,958 --> 01:06:36,583
I can't just change how I
feel about you that easily.

1329
01:06:39,416 --> 01:06:42,625
You think I like this crap
any more than you do!

1330
01:06:44,625 --> 01:06:46,500
The difference is
that I'm not giving up?!

1331
01:06:46,583 --> 01:06:49,250
I'll make sure
our friendship survives!

1332
01:06:58,041 --> 01:06:59,041
There's something
I've been wanting to

1333
01:06:59,125 --> 01:07:01,291
ask you for a long time.

1334
01:07:03,583 --> 01:07:05,625
You're a really
popular girl, right?

1335
01:07:05,708 --> 01:07:07,375
If you wanted to date
someone else, you wouldn't

1336
01:07:07,458 --> 01:07:09,250
have a hard time
finding somebody.

1337
01:07:09,333 --> 01:07:11,166
It doesn't make a
whole lot of sense.

1338
01:07:11,250 --> 01:07:13,666
So, why did you pick me?

1339
01:07:17,291 --> 01:07:18,083
Why you?

1340
01:07:18,166 --> 01:07:20,500
I don't have just one reason.

1341
01:07:23,791 --> 01:07:26,958
It's because I love you okay!

1342
01:07:57,958 --> 01:08:00,041
Thank you for your business!

1343
01:08:01,541 --> 01:08:03,041
Yo, Iketani!

1344
01:08:03,125 --> 01:08:04,208
Hey...

1345
01:08:04,291 --> 01:08:05,208
I heard the weather
guy saying it could

1346
01:08:05,291 --> 01:08:06,625
start dumping snow
on us anytime.

1347
01:08:06,708 --> 01:08:09,083
Sure feels cold enough
for that kinda thing tonight.

1348
01:08:09,166 --> 01:08:10,250
Tell me, Itsuki...

1349
01:08:10,333 --> 01:08:12,208
Got any big plans
brewing for Christmas?

1350
01:08:12,291 --> 01:08:13,708
Me?
My plans?

1351
01:08:13,791 --> 01:08:16,125
You wanna take a guess?

1352
01:08:16,208 --> 01:08:18,541
Party all night with a couple
of your closest friends.

1353
01:08:18,625 --> 01:08:20,208
Last Christmas of
your high school life.

1354
01:08:20,291 --> 01:08:21,291
Go out with a blast.

1355
01:08:21,375 --> 01:08:22,458
No way man.

1356
01:08:22,541 --> 01:08:24,083
I'm gonna be working
here all night long.

1357
01:08:24,166 --> 01:08:25,916
I gotta make enough
cash for some new tires.

1358
01:08:26,000 --> 01:08:27,708
My Levin needs studless
ones put on before

1359
01:08:27,791 --> 01:08:31,000
winter sets in and starts
jacking with my suspension.

1360
01:08:31,583 --> 01:08:33,541
You sound just like me.

1361
01:08:34,083 --> 01:08:36,083
Is Takumi doing anything?

1362
01:08:36,875 --> 01:08:37,958
Takumi?

1363
01:08:38,041 --> 01:08:39,541
Not sure.

1364
01:08:40,333 --> 01:08:42,041
He's been completely out of it.

1365
01:08:42,125 --> 01:08:43,125
Totally brain dead.

1366
01:08:43,208 --> 01:08:46,291
And today he's just been weird.

1367
01:08:58,250 --> 01:09:01,083
Hey dad, I, uh...

1368
01:09:01,166 --> 01:09:02,583
...um...

1369
01:09:02,666 --> 01:09:03,458
Look.

1370
01:09:03,541 --> 01:09:05,666
I'll be graduating pretty soon.

1371
01:09:06,000 --> 01:09:07,000
So I thought...

1372
01:09:07,083 --> 01:09:09,250
Do whatever you want.

1373
01:09:11,041 --> 01:09:13,250
You can take over the tofu shop.

1374
01:09:13,333 --> 01:09:14,750
Or not.
Whatever...

1375
01:09:14,833 --> 01:09:16,666
It's your call kid.

1376
01:09:34,291 --> 01:09:35,625
How is it that you
don't have anything

1377
01:09:35,708 --> 01:09:38,000
better to do on Christmas eve?

1378
01:09:38,083 --> 01:09:39,083
Loser!

1379
01:09:39,166 --> 01:09:41,083
Can't you find better
company to keep?

1380
01:09:41,166 --> 01:09:42,500
Don't say that!

1381
01:09:43,041 --> 01:09:44,541
It doesn't matter where I go.

1382
01:09:44,625 --> 01:09:47,083
It's a tough world for Mr.
Lonely out there guys.

1383
01:09:47,166 --> 01:09:48,250
Oh, I know!

1384
01:09:48,333 --> 01:09:49,416
Wherever you look there
are happy couples

1385
01:09:49,500 --> 01:09:51,458
cavorting around hand in hand!

1386
01:09:52,208 --> 01:09:54,250
Whaddya say we
all go out to eat huh?

1387
01:09:54,333 --> 01:09:55,250
Something nice?

1388
01:09:55,333 --> 01:09:56,791
Little fancy?

1389
01:09:56,875 --> 01:09:58,041
Yeah, I'm game.

1390
01:09:58,125 --> 01:09:59,833
Are you in, Itsuki?

1391
01:09:59,916 --> 01:10:01,375
You better believe
I'm going with you!

1392
01:10:01,458 --> 01:10:02,750
I got nothing else to do!

1393
01:10:02,833 --> 01:10:03,958
Takumi?

1394
01:10:04,041 --> 01:10:05,958
Sounds fun but I
don't have any money, so...

1395
01:10:06,041 --> 01:10:07,166
...no.

1396
01:10:08,625 --> 01:10:12,083
You can be so anti-social
sometimes, you know that?

1397
01:10:24,958 --> 01:10:26,125
Tofu shop.

1398
01:10:26,208 --> 01:10:26,958
There it is!

1399
01:10:27,041 --> 01:10:28,166
Finally.

1400
01:10:32,416 --> 01:10:34,416
'Kay here goes.

1401
01:10:34,500 --> 01:10:37,250
Sheesh, it's cold out here.

1402
01:10:38,500 --> 01:10:41,416
It'll be snowing on
the mountain, soon.

1403
01:10:41,500 --> 01:10:43,333
Hi, uh, I'm a friend of tofu's.

1404
01:10:43,416 --> 01:10:44,500
No, I'm sorry.

1405
01:10:44,583 --> 01:10:45,583
What I meant to say was that

1406
01:10:45,666 --> 01:10:47,250
I'm a friend of
Takumi's from school.

1407
01:10:47,333 --> 01:10:48,208
Oh, okay.

1408
01:10:48,291 --> 01:10:49,541
Takumi's friend.

1409
01:10:49,625 --> 01:10:52,333
Sorry, he hasn't come back
from his work runs yet.

1410
01:10:54,208 --> 01:10:56,375
All right.
Well, thank you.

1411
01:10:56,458 --> 01:10:57,958
I, uh...

1412
01:11:00,000 --> 01:11:01,125
Never mind.

1413
01:11:01,208 --> 01:11:02,375
It's nothing.

1414
01:11:02,458 --> 01:11:04,916
I hope you have a Merry
Christmas, goodnight.

1415
01:11:13,541 --> 01:11:14,625
She...

1416
01:11:14,708 --> 01:11:17,458
...kind of looks like
a homeless person.

1417
01:11:19,125 --> 01:11:20,791
Hold on a second, sweetheart.

1418
01:11:20,875 --> 01:11:22,250
Your bag looks a little heavy.

1419
01:11:22,333 --> 01:11:24,958
If you're here to see my
son, he'll be back soon.

1420
01:11:25,041 --> 01:11:27,125
Why don't you come
inside and warm up?

1421
01:11:27,208 --> 01:11:29,625
I can make you a cup of tea.

1422
01:11:29,708 --> 01:11:32,250
Okay!
If you don't mind!

1423
01:11:36,791 --> 01:11:37,958
Christmas...

1424
01:11:38,041 --> 01:11:40,416
It's always so boring.

1425
01:11:41,875 --> 01:11:44,416
I'd feed you, but we're
down to just tea.

1426
01:11:44,500 --> 01:11:45,958
Oh.

1427
01:11:46,041 --> 01:11:48,166
That's what you were carrying
in that giant bag of yours.

1428
01:11:48,250 --> 01:11:49,541
It's cute, don't you think?

1429
01:11:49,625 --> 01:11:52,500
It lights up like a real
tree and everything.

1430
01:11:53,083 --> 01:11:54,791
It's beautiful.

1431
01:11:56,541 --> 01:11:57,583
An Eight-Six?

1432
01:11:57,666 --> 01:11:59,000
A handmade Eight-Six.

1433
01:11:59,083 --> 01:12:00,541
I did it myself.

1434
01:12:00,625 --> 01:12:03,291
I know how much that
car means to Takumi.

1435
01:12:05,000 --> 01:12:07,833
Speaking of the kid, he must be
out wandering the streets again.

1436
01:12:07,916 --> 01:12:10,958
What time did you say you
two were supposed to meet?

1437
01:12:11,041 --> 01:12:12,166
Well, uh...

1438
01:12:12,250 --> 01:12:14,416
...we didn't set any
specific time, exactly.

1439
01:12:14,500 --> 01:12:18,166
I just wanted to come by and
wish Takumi a Merry Christmas.

1440
01:12:20,833 --> 01:12:22,083
I'll take these two.

1441
01:12:22,166 --> 01:12:23,375
Sure.

1442
01:12:32,041 --> 01:12:33,666
I've been wondering something.

1443
01:12:33,750 --> 01:12:36,708
You're that girl who kept
calling all summer, aren't you?

1444
01:12:36,791 --> 01:12:38,458
That was me.

1445
01:12:38,541 --> 01:12:40,750
But then you up and
stopped calling out of nowhere.

1446
01:12:40,833 --> 01:12:43,958
Guess I'm just curious as to
what happened with all of that?

1447
01:12:44,041 --> 01:12:45,875
Something did happen,
but I didn't think

1448
01:12:45,958 --> 01:12:46,916
it was that big a deal,

1449
01:12:47,000 --> 01:12:49,500
and now it's like
Takumi hates me.

1450
01:12:49,833 --> 01:12:51,000
I don't want to
graduate with things

1451
01:12:51,083 --> 01:12:52,708
like this between us,
so I'm doing everything

1452
01:12:52,791 --> 01:12:54,125
I can to bring it back around.

1453
01:12:54,208 --> 01:12:55,666
But he still hasn't forgiven me,

1454
01:12:55,750 --> 01:12:57,750
and I don't know
if he's going to.

1455
01:12:57,833 --> 01:13:00,166
I don't know what happened,
but that's his personality.

1456
01:13:00,250 --> 01:13:01,958
He's never been very
good at deciding whether

1457
01:13:02,041 --> 01:13:04,375
he should forgive
someone or hold a grudge.

1458
01:13:04,458 --> 01:13:05,708
That's just him.

1459
01:13:05,791 --> 01:13:07,458
But I don't think he hates you.

1460
01:13:07,541 --> 01:13:09,583
He may be a teenager,
but more often than not

1461
01:13:09,666 --> 01:13:11,958
he acts like he's
a stubborn old man.

1462
01:13:12,041 --> 01:13:14,000
Once he's made up
his mind about something,

1463
01:13:14,083 --> 01:13:16,625
the kid sticks to it,
no matter what.

1464
01:13:16,708 --> 01:13:18,125
And when things
don't work out the way

1465
01:13:18,208 --> 01:13:22,333
he wanted them to,
he can get a little obnoxious.

1466
01:13:22,416 --> 01:13:25,333
Prob'ly gets it
from his old man.

1467
01:13:36,166 --> 01:13:37,833
I'm home.

1468
01:13:41,375 --> 01:13:43,041
Who's here?

1469
01:13:46,833 --> 01:13:48,375
Merry Christmas, Takumi.

1470
01:13:48,458 --> 01:13:49,500
What's going on here?

1471
01:13:49,583 --> 01:13:50,708
What's this?

1472
01:13:50,791 --> 01:13:52,375
Surprise.

1473
01:13:52,458 --> 01:13:55,041
Dad, what the hell do
you think you're doing?

1474
01:13:55,375 --> 01:13:58,375
Merry Christmas!

1475
01:13:58,916 --> 01:13:59,500
This...

1476
01:13:59,583 --> 01:14:01,333
...is awesome!!

1477
01:14:01,416 --> 01:14:03,583
What should I sing next, guys?

1478
01:14:03,666 --> 01:14:07,416
How can he be like that without
a single drink in his system?

1479
01:14:07,750 --> 01:14:08,875
I'm lonely.

1480
01:14:08,958 --> 01:14:09,916
Yeah, and lame.

1481
01:14:10,000 --> 01:14:11,375
Oh, Mako.

1482
01:14:11,458 --> 01:14:12,791
Come on!

1483
01:14:12,875 --> 01:14:16,708
Road racers like us don't
need chicks anyway, do we?

1484
01:14:18,750 --> 01:14:21,083
Takumi, would you move the
tree off the table please?

1485
01:14:21,166 --> 01:14:22,625
Yeah, I got it.

1486
01:14:22,708 --> 01:14:24,833
I've loved Christmas
ever since I was a kid.

1487
01:14:24,916 --> 01:14:26,375
It's my favorite holiday.

1488
01:14:26,458 --> 01:14:28,208
So this year,
I wanted to make sure

1489
01:14:28,291 --> 01:14:30,083
I could celebrate it with you.

1490
01:14:31,041 --> 01:14:32,583
You said you hadn't
had a Christmas party

1491
01:14:32,666 --> 01:14:35,750
before and I thought this
was the perfect opportunity.

1492
01:14:39,041 --> 01:14:41,000
Well, don't just
sit there staring at it!

1493
01:14:41,083 --> 01:14:42,333
Let's eat this cake!

1494
01:14:42,416 --> 01:14:43,125
Great.

1495
01:14:43,208 --> 01:14:44,166
Yeah... sounds good to me.

1496
01:14:44,250 --> 01:14:45,916
Go on!
Light the candles!

1497
01:14:46,000 --> 01:14:47,166
Can I see your lighter, dad?

1498
01:14:47,250 --> 01:14:49,000
Oh... yeah.

1499
01:14:51,875 --> 01:14:53,500
Here go the lights.

1500
01:14:54,500 --> 01:14:56,166
All right.

1501
01:15:21,000 --> 01:15:23,625
Wow... I guess he
already went to sleep.

1502
01:15:30,291 --> 01:15:31,541
Huh?

1503
01:15:33,875 --> 01:15:35,041
So...

1504
01:15:35,125 --> 01:15:36,833
What are you going
to do after you graduate?

1505
01:15:36,916 --> 01:15:38,458
I haven't decided yet.

1506
01:15:38,541 --> 01:15:40,083
How about you?

1507
01:15:40,583 --> 01:15:41,625
Not yet.

1508
01:15:41,708 --> 01:15:43,000
I've been giving it
a lot of thought.

1509
01:15:43,083 --> 01:15:44,708
And I just don't
think I can stay here

1510
01:15:44,791 --> 01:15:46,416
and keep working
at the burger place.

1511
01:15:46,500 --> 01:15:48,333
I need to find
something permanent.

1512
01:15:48,416 --> 01:15:50,208
So I'm thinking
of going to school.

1513
01:15:50,291 --> 01:15:52,166
in Tokyo.

1514
01:16:01,333 --> 01:16:02,291
We'd all like to say...

1515
01:16:02,375 --> 01:16:03,583
Thank you!

1516
01:16:04,375 --> 01:16:06,375
And a very happy
new year to you, sir.

1517
01:16:06,458 --> 01:16:07,833
Happy new year to you, too.

1518
01:16:07,916 --> 01:16:09,291
Now, being the start
of the year there

1519
01:16:09,375 --> 01:16:10,541
could be a lot of new customers.

1520
01:16:10,625 --> 01:16:11,666
I want you guys doing your best.

1521
01:16:11,750 --> 01:16:12,875
So get your hustle on today.

1522
01:16:12,958 --> 01:16:14,791
Well, you can count on me, boss!

1523
01:16:14,875 --> 01:16:15,666
Me!

1524
01:16:15,750 --> 01:16:17,000
You're pretty keyed up, Itsuki.

1525
01:16:17,083 --> 01:16:18,375
That's right, I am!

1526
01:16:18,458 --> 01:16:19,916
I'll be starting
full time in April,

1527
01:16:20,000 --> 01:16:22,500
and I wanna have a
good lead in to that.

1528
01:16:22,958 --> 01:16:24,833
Gotta clean up over there.

1529
01:16:25,291 --> 01:16:27,750
You mean in April I have to
start seeing him every day.

1530
01:16:27,833 --> 01:16:29,458
I don't know if I should
be happy about that or

1531
01:16:29,541 --> 01:16:31,833
start crying my little eyes out.

1532
01:16:31,916 --> 01:16:33,541
Takumi, don't just
stand there like a statue,

1533
01:16:33,625 --> 01:16:34,708
get to cleaning those windows!

1534
01:16:34,791 --> 01:16:35,916
